Using the cgi module
Begin by writing import cgi.

When you write a new script, consider adding these lines:

import cgitb
cgitb.enable()
This activates a special exception handler that will display detailed reports in the Web browser if any errors occur. If youâ€™d rather not show the guts of your program to users of your script, you can have the reports saved to files instead, with code like this:

import cgitb
cgitb.enable(display=0, logdir="/path/to/logdir")
